85628969-d482-4f49-ad71-2721caed3ed6	لَعَلَّكُم تَعقِلونَ	So that you may understand / use reason	Al-Baqarah 2:73, 2:242 and others	When you want listeners to comprehend your message with intellect and reasoning. Used to encourage critical thinking and understanding.	short	2	Invitation to intellectual engagement and mindful comprehension	1	teaching, persuasion, explanation	formal
90ab98e0-e425-4541-ae3e-e19db346b342	نَحنُ نَقُصُّ عَلَيكَ أَحسَنَ القَصَصِ	We relate to you the best of stories	Yusuf 12:3	When you want to tell someone a beautiful or meaningful story. Expresses the value and beauty of the narrative you're about to share.	short	2	Appreciation for storytelling as a means of wisdom and moral teaching	1	storytelling, teaching, sharing experiences	formal
e4417791-2d09-4d93-9831-7c4a72cbf02b	وَإِن كُنتَ مِن قَبلِهِ لَمِنَ الغافِلينَ	And indeed you were, before this, among the heedless	Yusuf 12:3	When you want to express that you were previously unaware or heedless but then learned and understood something important.	short	3	Acknowledgment of past ignorance and celebration of newfound awareness	1	self-reflection, learning, personal growth	formal
15c65e04-0b69-4567-acd4-e8b2cec7a1e2	يا أَبَتِ	O my father	Yusuf 12:4, Maryam 19:42-45, and others	A tender and respectful way to address one's father, combining affection with honor. Used when speaking to or calling one's father.	short	1	Respectful and loving address to a father figure	1	family, addressing elders	conversational
3540cb9e-150d-441f-aa0c-b5dad6584cd2	يا بُنَيَّ	O my dear son / my child	Luqman 31:13, 31:16-17, and others	A tender and affectionate way to address one's son or a young person. Expresses care, guidance, and paternal affection.	short	1	Affectionate address to a child or younger person, implying mentorship and care	1	family, mentoring, guidance	conversational
86481fc3-fe51-40dc-be1e-b0d91dde56ba	لا تَقصُص رُؤياكَ	Do not relate your vision / dream	Yusuf 12:5	Advice not to reveal one's plans, dreams, or visions to everyone. Used to counsel discretion and protection of one's aspirations from envy or harm.	short	2	Wisdom of protecting one's dreams and plans from those who might wish ill	1	advice, protection, discretion	formal
1fdcc00d-b525-496c-aaba-3d771e2e4019	فَيَكيدوا لَكَ كَيداً	And they will plot against you a plot	Yusuf 12:5	Warning about hidden schemes or plots against you. Used to alert someone about potential deception or conspiracy.	short	2	Awareness of hidden dangers and the need for vigilance	1	warning, caution, awareness	formal
66bf7782-69db-45f2-a561-d0c7b9db1cdd	إِنَّ الشَّيطانَ لِلإِنسانِ عَدُوٌّ مُبينٌ	Indeed, Satan is to mankind a clear enemy	Yusuf 12:5	Reminder that Satan is humanity's true and obvious enemy. Used to attribute temptation or wrongdoing to satanic influence and to warn against evil.	short	2	Recognition of the spiritual battle and the need to resist evil temptations	1	warning, spiritual guidance, moral teaching	formal
136e15be-d6f3-424d-85ac-ec54fd639102	وَكَذلِكَ يَجتَبيكَ	And thus will your Lord choose you	Yusuf 12:6	Expression indicating that someone is being chosen or selected. Used to convey divine or special selection and honor.	short	2	Divine selection and favor, recognition of special purpose	1	encouragement, recognition, spiritual growth	formal
b4c00583-5575-44e7-9268-34367d9c93c8	تَأويلَ الأَحاديثِ	The interpretation of narratives / dreams	Yusuf 12:6, 12:21	Reference to the interpretation or explanation of stories, dreams, or events. Used when requesting or discussing the meaning behind narratives.	short	3	Seeking deeper meaning and understanding beyond surface appearances	1	explanation, interpretation, wisdom	formal
df70d1b8-2be1-4643-a43e-8e5dcdde9f49	يُتِمَّ نِعمَتَهُ	He completes His favor / blessing	Yusuf 12:6, Al-Ma'idah 5:3	Expression meaning 'to complete a favor or blessing.' Used when someone completes their kindness or when acknowledging the completion of divine blessings.	short	2	Completion and perfection of divine grace and blessings	1	gratitude, blessing, completion	formal
038b9f26-1c16-44d9-9716-e7d061863dc0	آياتٍ لِلسّائِلينَ	Signs for those who inquire / ask	Yusuf 12:7	Reference to signs, lessons, or evidence for those who seek understanding. Used when pointing to clear indicators or lessons for thoughtful seekers.	short	2	Knowledge and wisdom revealed to those who genuinely seek understanding	1	teaching, guidance, evidence	formal
7bff0c38-d217-4ec5-82fc-051ed58f8bac	وَنَحنُ عُصبَةٌ	While we are a group / strong band	Yusuf 12:8	Expression indicating you are a strong group or united team. Used to emphasize collective strength, unity, and solidarity.	short	2	Strength in unity and collective effort	1	teamwork, unity, strength	conversational
f40a9064-0973-4428-9567-e618cde9dc26	أَحَبُّ إِلَىٰ أَبِينَا مِنَّا	More beloved to our father than us	Yusuf 12:8	Expression of perceived unfairness in love or treatment. Used when feeling that someone shows favoritism towards another person.	short	2	Recognition of jealousy and the need to address feelings of inequality	1	family, emotions, fairness	conversational
0b45d041-f193-40ae-9ff6-dd95a8507ef8	إِنَّ أَبَانَا لَفِي ضَلَالٍ مُّبِينٍ	Indeed, our father is in clear error	Yusuf 12:8	Expression that someone close is making a clear mistake in judgment or dealing with a situation.	short	3	Recognizing when loved ones make errors in judgment	1	advice, disagreement, concern	formal
e85a4868-8443-4c86-adfc-9a04f334a38f	اطۡرَحُوهُ أَرۡضًا	Cast him out to some distant land	Yusuf 12:9	Metaphor for completely getting rid of someone or distancing them. Reflects the idea of total removal or exclusion.	short	3	Warning against extreme solutions driven by jealousy	1	conflict, exclusion, warning	formal
0949f67b-1546-4356-8ef3-bdae58f7f51f	يَخۡلُ لَكُمۡ وَجۡهُ أَبِيكُمۡ	The countenance of your father will be exclusively for you	Yusuf 12:9	Desire to monopolize someone's attention, love, or favor - whether a parent, leader, or authority figure.	short	2	Recognition of the human desire for exclusive attention and approval	1	family, workplace, attention-seeking	formal
50198280-74b2-4bc3-9b52-47bb279db90c	قَوۡمٗا صَٰلِحِينَ	Righteous people	Yusuf 12:9	Used to describe good, righteous people. A positive description of character.	short	1	Aspiration towards righteousness and good character	1	description, character, praise	formal
6b3ef6a8-4a76-43e2-8a6e-d1b5aef04f83	لَا تَقۡتُلُواْ يُوسُفَ	Do not kill Yusuf	Yusuf 12:10	Used to reject oppression or aggression against an innocent person. A call to protect the vulnerable.	short	2	Standing against injustice and protecting the innocent	1	justice, protection, advocacy	formal
4a8b4e87-735e-4fa9-ba04-a15df016464a	وَأَلۡقُوهُ فِي غَيَٰبَتِ ٱلۡجُبِّ	And throw him into the bottom of the well	Yusuf 12:10, 12:15	Metaphor for hiding someone or something in a deep, concealed place. Used to describe concealment or suppression.	short	3	Hidden problems or suppressed truths that will eventually surface	1	concealment, secrets, suppression	formal
68805067-9bb9-4a9f-869a-456e0a2fb43a	يَلۡتَقِطۡهُ بَعۡضُ ٱلسَّيَّارَةِ	Some caravan will pick him up	Yusuf 12:10	Suggestion that a stranger or unexpected person will find something/someone. Reminds us that relief can come from unexpected sources.	short	2	Hope that strangers may be the means of relief and rescue	1	hope, rescue, unexpected help	formal
a1675af9-e832-42f5-a6e0-a346c2f8d26a	إِن كُنتُمۡ فَٰعِلِينَ	If you are to do [it]	Yusuf 12:11	Conditional phrase questioning a group's intention to execute an idea. Used to challenge or confirm commitment.	short	2	Testing commitment and sincerity in action	1	challenge, commitment, questioning	formal
9cf08c6c-ec3f-4c84-aacc-5866b4665173	يَٰٓأَبَانَا مَا لَكَ لَا تَأۡمَنَّا	O our father, why do you not trust us	Yusuf 12:11	Expression of feeling hurt when someone doesn't trust you despite your love or good intentions.	short	2	The pain of mistrust and the desire to prove oneself trustworthy	1	family, trust, emotions	conversational
6c43e2e0-fb12-4b6d-8453-f9cfb9a61d7b	وَإِنَّا لَهُۥ لَنَٰصِحُونَ	And indeed, we are his sincere well-wishers	Yusuf 12:11	Affirmation of good intentions and sincere advice to someone who doubts you.	short	2	Asserting sincerity when facing suspicion	1	sincerity, trust, assurance	formal
b1470068-7103-4f70-860d-1b76e74878c1	أَرۡسِلۡهُ مَعَنَا غَدٗا يَرۡتَعۡ وَيَلۡعَبۡ	Send him with us tomorrow that he may enjoy himself and play	Yusuf 12:12	Request to let someone join you for leisure and play. Used when inviting someone for recreation.	short	2	The importance of recreation and trust in relationships	1	invitation, recreation, family	conversational
e94f889d-51d4-42f5-b4b6-11bea62f26a7	وَإِنَّا لَهُۥ لَحَٰفِظُونَ	And indeed, we will be his guardians	Yusuf 12:12	Promise to protect and preserve someone or something entrusted to you.	short	2	Commitment to responsibility and trustworthiness	1	promise, protection, responsibility	formal
dff13317-4d09-445d-b744-3b2d8a41cd89	إِنِّي لَيَحۡزُنُنِيٓ أَن تَذۡهَبُواْ بِهِۦ	Indeed, it saddens me that you should take him	Yusuf 12:13	Expression of deep sadness about being separated from someone you care about.	short	2	Natural parental concern and fear of separation	1	emotions, separation, concern	formal
0cef529b-5135-4e15-8637-e12ad48fb1f3	وَأَخَافُ أَن يَأۡكُلَهُ ٱلذِّئۡبُ	And I fear that a wolf should devour him	Yusuf 12:13	Expression of specific fear about a particular danger threatening someone or something precious to you.	short	2	Parental anxiety and protective instinct	1	fear, protection, concern	formal
43ac6681-6519-4e84-a4a0-a8cd1baf0843	وَنَحۡنُ عُصۡبَةٌ إِنَّآ إِذٗا لَّخَٰسِرُونَ	While we are a [strong] group? Indeed, we would then be losers	Yusuf 12:14	Emphasis that your strong group cannot possibly fail or fall into such weakness.	short	2	Overconfidence and the need for humility	1	teamwork, confidence, challenge	conversational
b92c52d9-9b3c-4e4c-9ae5-a5950ee7aec0	فَلَمَّا ذَهَبُواْ بِهِۦ	So when they took him away	Yusuf 12:15	Used when recalling the moment someone left with others. Narrative phrase for storytelling.	short	2	The beginning of a journey or trial	1	storytelling, narrative, recollection	formal
a9eff93a-a2e1-4a39-a40b-7439a71de7c0	وَأَجۡمَعُوٓاْ أَن يَجۡعَلُوهُ فِي غَيَٰبَتِ ٱلۡجُبِّ	And they all agreed to put him into the bottom of the well	Yusuf 12:15	Describes a deliberate collective plan to harm someone secretly. Summarizes hidden conspiracy.	short	3	Warning against collective wrongdoing and secret plots	1	conspiracy, warning, collective action	formal
5eae9579-e3e1-411c-bbe4-8c67b444f2ec	لَتُنَبِّئَنَّهُم بِأَمۡرِهِمۡ هَٰذَا	You will surely inform them of this affair of theirs	Yusuf 12:15	Comfort that wrongdoers will eventually be confronted with the truth of their actions.	short	3	Divine promise that truth will prevail	1	justice, truth, consolation	formal
f4c56557-d518-4b0d-9fa5-43a13c837196	وَجَآءُوٓ أَبَاهُمۡ عِشَآءٗ يَبۡكُونَ	And they came to their father at night, weeping	Yusuf 12:16	Description of fake crying and pretense of grief. Used to describe theatrical sorrow.	short	2	Warning against deception and false emotions	1	deception, emotions, warning	formal
51864017-75d9-4c86-bc98-1dd5b6093d81	إِنَّا ذَهَبۡنَا نَسۡتَبِقُ	Indeed, we went racing	Yusuf 12:17	Used to describe participation in a race or competition. Can be literal or metaphorical.	short	1	Innocent activities that can become excuses for negligence	1	sports, competition, activities	conversational
de0f7f81-65fb-46d2-9843-3eb2a896a39d	عِندَ مَتَٰعِنَا	With our possessions	Yusuf 12:17	Description of something left near belongings or baggage.	short	1	Negligence in guarding what is precious	1	belongings, location, description	conversational
e4352523-cd9d-4196-9837-5c7ef516b60d	فَأَكَلَهُ ٱلذِّئۡبُ	And a wolf devoured him	Yusuf 12:17	Excuse used by liars for loss of something precious. A fabricated reason for disappearance.	short	2	Classic false excuse and the consequences of deception	1	excuses, deception, loss	formal
67e0187b-c50c-4bc3-9313-a5f0e7279f93	وَمَآ أَنتَ بِمُؤۡمِنٖ لَّنَا وَلَوۡ كُنَّا صَٰدِقِينَ	And you would not believe us, even if we were truthful	Yusuf 12:17	Expression that the other party will not believe you no matter what you say, even if you're telling the truth.	short	2	The tragedy of broken trust	1	trust, communication, frustration	formal
286ebebc-204f-4d8c-85fa-87e6080addb0	وَجَآءُو عَلَىٰ قَمِيصِهِۦ بِدَمٖ كَذِبٖ	And they brought upon his shirt false blood	Yusuf 12:18	Description of fabricated evidence used to cover a crime. Metaphor for false proof.	short	3	Warning against manufacturing false evidence	1	deception, evidence, crime	formal
3ea4433e-1bef-43c5-8603-34a58a5ee0a8	بَلۡ سَوَّلَتۡ لَكُمۡ أَنفُسُكُمۡ أَمۡرٗا	Rather, your souls have enticed you to something	Yusuf 12:18, 12:83	Recognition that one's own self/desires have made evil seem attractive. Describes self-deception.	short	3	The danger of following base desires	1	self-reflection, temptation, psychology	formal
e66aeab0-a7d2-4bfc-aebb-7b67028aeb0c	فَصَبۡرٞ جَمِيلٞ	So patience is most fitting	Yusuf 12:18, 12:83	Beautiful, dignified patience when facing calamity. A motto for accepting divine decree gracefully.	short	2	The nobility of patience without complaint	1	patience, coping, resilience	formal
b39dc1a6-d9fd-4139-b02a-106380cd731a	وَٱللَّهُ ٱلۡمُسۡتَعَانُ عَلَىٰ مَا تَصِفُونَ	And Allah is the One sought for help against what you describe	Yusuf 12:18	Reliance on Allah when facing false accusations and lies. Used when unable to defend against slander.	short	2	Trust in divine justice when human justice fails	1	reliance, defense, accusations	formal
a92f8546-b19c-4c34-a11a-40506380bd53	وَجَآءَتۡ سَيَّارَةٞ	And there came a caravan	Yusuf 12:19	Narrative phrase describing the arrival of travelers. Used in storytelling about journeys.	short	1	Unexpected arrivals that change destiny	1	storytelling, travel, arrival	formal
1a6dcab0-25d2-43f4-bb7e-9e0f435a1469	فَأَدۡلَىٰ دَلۡوَهُۥ	And he let down his bucket	Yusuf 12:19	Someone starting a simple task and discovering a great treasure. Metaphor for unexpected findings.	short	2	Small actions leading to great discoveries	1	discovery, action, fortune	formal
587e6b3d-05cb-4426-9b5c-9bf84dd45dc0	يَٰبُشۡرَىٰ هَٰذَا غُلَٰمٞ	Good news! Here is a boy	Yusuf 12:19	Exclamation of joy upon finding a child or receiving a new blessing. Expression of happy surprise.	short	1	Joy at unexpected blessings	1	celebration, joy, good news	conversational
a37b589d-7950-4e86-bb80-a84239869946	وَأَسَرُّوهُ بِضَٰعَةٗ	And they concealed him as merchandise	Yusuf 12:19	Hiding someone's true identity and treating them as mere commodity. Dehumanization.	short	3	Warning against reducing humans to objects	1	deception, exploitation, trafficking	formal
2ee95a69-3a60-4170-8f20-f50b5aa99c17	وَٱللَّهُ عَلِيمُۢ بِمَا يَعۡمَلُونَ	And Allah is Knowing of what they do	Yusuf 12:19, and others	Reminder that Allah sees all actions. Used to affirm divine awareness and accountability.	short	1	Divine omniscience and ultimate accountability	1	awareness, accountability, faith	formal
bdaf3919-0809-4f4a-acb7-67c82b6866bd	وَشَرَوۡهُ بِثَمَنۢ بَخۡسٖ	And they sold him for a reduced price	Yusuf 12:20	Selling something precious for far less than its worth. Undervaluing talent or blessings.	short	2	Warning against undervaluing precious gifts	1	trade, value, exploitation	formal
c7f6f829-cc86-4450-a16f-e282510e35c2	دَرَٰهِمَ مَعۡدُودَةٖ	A few dirhams	Yusuf 12:20	Describes a very small amount of money. Used to emphasize triviality of payment.	short	1	The insignificance of worldly gain compared to true worth	1	money, value, description	formal
0f052d03-4e4a-4344-808f-2250a5f234b0	وَكَانُواْ فِيهِ مِنَ ٱلزَّٰهِدِينَ	And they were, concerning him, of those content to sell	Yusuf 12:20	People who squandered a great blessing because they didn't recognize its value.	short	2	Warning against failing to recognize blessings	1	appreciation, regret, value	formal
f3940b91-48a4-4a42-9a27-bec48a078aa3	كَمَآ أَتَمَّهَا عَلَىٰٓ أَبَوَيۡكَ مِن قَبۡلُ	As He completed it upon your forefathers before	Yusuf 12:6	Recognition that Allah completes a series of blessings upon you as He did upon your ancestors.	short	2	Continuity of divine favor across generations	1	gratitude, family legacy, blessings	formal
b64ddef2-c6b8-4c75-888e-8559b4daff75	وَتَرَكۡنَا يُوسُفَ عِندَ مَتَٰعِنَا	And we left Yusuf with our possessions	Yusuf 12:17	Negligence in guarding what was entrusted to you. Used to describe abandonment of responsibility.	short	2	The consequences of negligence and broken trust	1	responsibility, negligence, trust	formal
38731bfa-b611-48e7-a356-e9fecff59c50	لَتُنَبِّئَنَّهُم بِأَمۡرِهِمۡ هَٰذَا وَهُمۡ لَا يَشۡعُرُونَ	You will surely inform them of this affair while they perceive not	Yusuf 12:15	Comfort that oppressors will one day learn the truth of their actions when they least expect it.	short	3	Divine timing in revealing truth and delivering justice	1	justice, consolation, truth	formal
65338414-2a4d-4893-abbf-464dc973c091	إِنَّ رَبَّكَ عَلِيمٌ حَكِيمٌ	Indeed, your Lord is Knowing and Wise	Yusuf 12:6, 12:83, and others	Reminder of Allah's perfect knowledge and wisdom. Used to accept things beyond our understanding.	short	1	Trust in divine wisdom beyond human comprehension	1	faith, trust, acceptance	formal
\.
